him from the assassination of Bobby Kennedy to the Vietnam war, the Khmer Rouge and the plight of indigenous people in his native Australia. He has successfully made the jump to feature documentaries, including Utopia and The War on Democracy. </p> <p>Along the way, Pilger has condemned western intervention in Iraq and Central America, supported Julian Assange and criticised Barack Obama’s military tactics. In his book The New Rulers of the World, he explored globalisation and its impact on the world’s poor, from Indonesia to Australia and beyond. </p> <p>With the book <a href=\"http://www.versobooks.com/books/842-the-new-rulers-of-the-world\">reissued next month with new material</a>, Pilger joins us to answers your questions about anything in his career, in a live webchat from 10am GMT (9pm EST) onwards on Wednesday 24 February. Post them in the comments below, and he’ll answer as many as possible.</p> </div>   <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2016-02-22T11:36:43.537Z\">at 11.36am GMT</time></p>  </div>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4hvjg","wordcount":"148","thumbnail":"http://media.guim.co.uk/80b282662a671ae09baeedf463a2e9f95e57acd4/435_180_2662_1598/140.jpg","commentCloseDate":"2016-02-24T13:00:00Z","standfirst":"<p>The firebrand journalist will be answering your questions in a live webchat from 10am GMT on Wednesday 24 February – post them in the comments below</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/books/live/2016/feb/22/john-pilger-webchat-the-new-rulers-of-the-world","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/books/live/2016/feb/22/john-pilger-webchat-the-new-rulers-of-the-world","sectionName":"Books","elements":[{"id":"80b282662a671ae09baeedf463a2e9f95e57acd4","relation":"main","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","file":"http://media.guim.co.uk/80b282662a671ae09baeedf463a2e9f95e57acd4/435_180_2662_1598/2000.jpg","typeData":{"copyright":"Felix Clay","picdarUrn":"GD*20309421","mediaApiUri":"https:/